column61: Departing station 93/26.7, heading to SCCOOOS.  Off effort due to speed=5.5kts
Associated with birds (gulls, cormorants, pelicans) and LO. Possible feeding.
Associated with pinn S#1. Possible feeding

with birds. Associated with Pinn S#2 and S#2.
w/birds, confirmed sighting w/ big eyes. Pinn S#2 and S#3 associated

S#4 a subgroup of these animals.
bow rode for a few minutes.
Ending observations to pull in array.  Arriving st. 93/40
single blow, not strong. Small dark whale back, maybe minke or beaked whale? Sighted by birder. **changed 2 May 2008 to on effort sighting--ABD**
2 smaller sized animals surfaced in front of ship and moved off slowly.
pulling in array, coming into st.93/50. Pulling in array.
heavy patches of fog moving in
bridge switching on fog horn. Breaking obs due to poor visibility
returning to obs, fog is lifting.
sighted by birder, Mike Bentley.  **changed 2 May 2008 to on effort sighting--ABD**
ending obs for dinner and to pull in array, arriving st.93/80.

acoustics picked up whistles. Animals too far off w/bad lighting to determine species.  Body shape and surface activity may indicate Dsp.
heading from SCCOOS station from st.90/30
